<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.4.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en"/><updated>2025-11-26T16:00:08+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">roamr</title><subtitle>UWaterloo Mechatronics Group 16 Capstone website. </subtitle><entry><title type="html">Communication and Interfacing</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/communication/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Communication and Interfacing"/><published>2025-11-23T14:40:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-11-23T14:40:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/communication</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/communication/"><![CDATA[<ul> <li>Added Bluetooth connection response to the ESP-32, which will allow teleoperated control from the phone, and is also required for WASM communicating and running with motors.</li> <li>Added communication from phone to any browser, allowing a user to teleoperate when the phone is attached to a robot.</li> </ul>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Anders and Thomason]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Integration</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/integration/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Integration"/><published>2025-11-23T14:40:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-11-23T14:40:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/integration</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/integration/"><![CDATA[<p>The whole team got together to put together a working prototype of the robot.</p> <div class="row mt-6"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-6"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/factory.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> The team hard at work. </div> <p><br/> <br/> <br/></p> <div class="row mt-6"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-6 d-flex justify-content-center"> <div style="transform: rotate(270deg); display: inline-block;"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/robot_v0.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> </div> <p><br/> <br/> <br/> <br/></p> <div class="caption"> roamr v0! </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Whole team]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Software Infrastructure</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/infra/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Software Infrastructure"/><published>2025-11-17T14:40:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-11-17T14:40:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/infra</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/infra/"><![CDATA[<p>We switched from the third-party WASMKit library to the officially supported WebAssembly WAMR library due to the lack of support in WASMKit for multi-threading. Now, WAMR allows us to compile into a file that can be interfaced with our app. Inside the WAMR library, we enabled certain flags that will become useful for our robot development:</p> <ul> <li>Shared memory</li> <li>Threads</li> <li>Neural networks</li> </ul> <p>Thomason also built out a feature that lets us call Swift function bindings from C++ code, thereby minimizing the amount of Swift code that users will have to touch in the future.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[WAMR backend by Thomason and Anders]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">BLE Demo</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/ble-demo/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="BLE Demo"/><published>2025-11-04T14:40:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-11-04T14:40:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/ble-demo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/ble-demo/"><![CDATA[<p>Olivia created a basic demo to show basic Bluetooth Low Energy phone-to-microcontroller communication.</p> <div class="row justify-content-sm-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/esp_1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" title="example image" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-5 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/esp_2.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" title="example image" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <ul> <li>ESP hooked up to laptop for serial monitoring</li> <li>Connecting to the ESP32 through my phone using NRC-connect and sending it a message</li> <li>The ESP-32 gets the message over BLE and laptop prints it out on the terminal serial monitor</li> </ul>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[BLE phone-microcontroller interface by Olivia]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Basic roamr app</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/basic-app/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Basic roamr app"/><published>2025-11-03T14:40:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-11-03T14:40:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/basic-app</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/basic-app/"><![CDATA[<p>To validate our sensor-reading ability through iOS APIs, Anders created a basic app (roamr v0.0!) that reads and displays the following:</p> <ul> <li>LiDAR data: mesh visualization and new point count</li> <li>Accelerometer: x, y, z acceleration</li> <li>Gyro visualization</li> </ul> <div class="row justify-content-center mt-3"> <div class="col-sm-8 col-md-6"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/roamr0.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <div class="caption text-center mt-2"> First iteration of roamr app </div> </div> </div> ]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="Nath"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Basic app by Anders]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Basic mapping and localization</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/basic-mapandloc/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Basic mapping and localization"/><published>2025-11-03T14:40:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-11-03T14:40:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/basic-mapandloc</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/basic-mapandloc/"><![CDATA[<p>To validate our software architecture, Kai built a basic “mapping and localization” demonstration.</p> <p>To recap, we are aiming to use minimize the need for users to do development in Swift/XCode and allow them to write code in C++, which is then compiled to WASM to run on the phone. To this end, we put together a basic demo with WASMKit.</p> <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bPDcQqSxsOI">Video demo</a></p> <div class="row justify-content-center mt-3"> <div class="col-sm-8 col-md-10"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/mapandloc.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <div class="caption text-center mt-2"> Mapping and localization idea </div> </div> </div> <p>In this demo, the sensor reading for LiDAR and IMU pose is done from Swift. Point cloud and pose information is then written to map form using a C++ backend (compiled to WASM).</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Basic mapping and localization by Kai]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">CAD</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/CAD/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="CAD"/><published>2025-10-19T14:40:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-10-19T14:40:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/CAD</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/CAD/"><![CDATA[<div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/Motor_Mount_Sketch.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> Motor Mount Sketch </div> <div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/Bottom_Body_Sketch.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> Bottom Body Sketch </div> <div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/CAD_V1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> CAD </div> <div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/CAD_V1_Explode.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> CAD Exploded View </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="Nathan"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[CAD Designs by Nathan]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Concept Sketches</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/concepts/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Concept Sketches"/><published>2025-10-07T14:52:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-10-07T14:52:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/concepts</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/concepts/"><![CDATA[<div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/nathan_sketch2.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> </div> <div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/kai_sketch.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> </div> <div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/anders_sketch.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> </div> <div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/olivia_sketch.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Design ideas]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Morphological Chart</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/morphological-chart/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Morphological Chart"/><published>2025-10-06T14:52:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-10-06T14:52:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/morphological-chart</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/morphological-chart/"><![CDATA[<div class="w-100 mt-3"> <figure> <picture> <img src="/assets/img/morphological_chart.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1 w-100" width="auto" height="auto" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> Morphological chart of components </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Comparison of component designs]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Decision Matrix</title><link href="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/decisionmatrix/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Decision Matrix"/><published>2025-10-06T14:51:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-10-06T14:51:00+00:00</updated><id>https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/decisionmatrix</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://uwtron16.github.io/blog/decisionmatrix/"><![CDATA[<table> <thead> <tr> <th>Criteria</th> <th style="text-align: right">Weight</th> <th style="text-align: right">Option A Score (1–5)</th> <th style="text-align: right">A Weighted</th> <th style="text-align: right">Option B Score</th> <th style="text-align: right">B Weighted</th> <th style="text-align: right">Option C Score</th> <th style="text-align: right">C Weighted</th> <th style="text-align: right">Option D Score</th> <th style="text-align: right">D Weighted</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td><strong>Cost</strong> (closer to <strong>under $500</strong> is better)</td> <td style="text-align: right">15</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Size</strong> (smaller is better)</td> <td style="text-align: right">8</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Open source</strong> (deps &amp; hardware)</td> <td style="text-align: right">8</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Weight</strong> (lighter is better)</td> <td style="text-align: right">8</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Mobility</strong> (climb slope &lt;15° comfortably)</td> <td style="text-align: right">8</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Modularity</strong> (expand with arms/legs/sensors)</td> <td style="text-align: right">10</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>HW functionality</strong> (modular/repairable; works w/ non-LiDAR iPhone)</td> <td style="text-align: right">8</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Durability</strong> (survive full-speed collision)</td> <td style="text-align: right">10</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Cycle time</strong> (more runtime is better)</td> <td style="text-align: right">10</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>SW functionality</strong> (PtP nav, SLAM, safety, LiDAR 4–5 m, map reuse, teleop, export data, calibration &lt;1 cm/5°, GPS)</td> <td style="text-align: right">15</td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>TOTAL</strong></td> <td style="text-align: right"><strong>100</strong></td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"><strong>=Σ</strong></td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"><strong>=Σ</strong></td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"><strong>=Σ</strong></td> <td style="text-align: right"> </td> <td style="text-align: right"><strong>=Σ</strong></td> </tr> </tbody> </table>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Preliminary decision matrix]]></summary></entry></feed>